MBOMBELA – SAPS spokesman Capt Zandile Gwaqa said Rudolph Phetla (31) was walking on the R40 when he was struck by a car near Drum Rock at about 22:00. “We need to find his family or he will be buried in a pauper’s grave.” ALSO READ: SPAR Lowveld spreads love for children in distress The police request the family or anyone who can assist to urgently contact Det Const Ngxam on
013-759-1286 or 079-764-9840.